    "content": "The Republican-controlled North Carolina Supreme Court reversing previous rulings that were handed down when the state Supreme Court leaned Democratic said Friday that North Carolinas constitution ga\u2026 [+10408 chars]",
    "summary": "The Republican-controlled North Carolina Supreme Court ruled that partisan gerrymandering is not within the authority of the state court to regulate, reversing previous rulings made by the Democratic-leaning court. The verdict was a victory for North Carolina's GOP state legislature, which brought the case before the state Supreme Court, and had failed to win a similar case before the US Supreme Court. The ruling bars voting rights groups from going to state court in the future to bring claims of extreme partisan gerrymandering against North Carolina maps. The decision also means Republicans can move forward with partisan gerrymandering and fortify their advantages in the US House of Representatives.",
