    "publishedAt": "2023-04-28T17:26:26Z",
    "content": "Despite suffering a significant blow this week in its attempt to take over Activision Blizzard\r\n, Microsoft\r\n still believes it can get the job done. The company has signed a 10-year agreement with S\u2026 [+2560 chars]",
    "summary": "Despite facing a major setback in its proposed takeover of Activision Blizzard, Microsoft has signed a 10-year agreement with Spanish cloud gaming provider Nware to offer its in-house PC games as well as Activision Blizzard titles, if the $68.7bn deal goes through. The partnership, along with previous agreements, is expected to make popular games available on more cloud game streaming services, according to Brad Smith, Microsoft's president and vice-chair. The deal comes after the UK's Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) blocked the takeover, citing Microsoft's dominant position in the cloud gaming market. Microsoft and Activision Blizzard plan to appeal the decision.",
