    "summary": "Senator Marco Rubio has expressed concerns about the recent dispute between Disney and Florida Governor Ron DeSantis, warning that it could put off other businesses from operating in the state. Disney has sued DeSantis over moves to restrict the company's self-governing status in Florida, which gives it similar powers to a local government in a special district. The feud began in 2022 when the company opposed legislation to restrict discussions about sexual orientation and gender identity in Florida schools.  Rubio has defended DeSantis, but has warned that the political battles could result in the state being viewed as an unfriendly environment for businesses to operate.",
