    "summary": "At least 25 people have been killed in a wave of Russian air strikes on cities across Ukraine, including Kyiv, according to officials. In Uman, a nine-storey residential building partially collapsed after being hit by a missile. A woman and her three-year-old daughter were killed in Dnipro, while in the central city of Uman, 23 people died, including four children. Russia said it had targeted Ukrainian army reserve units with high-precision weapons. More than 10 hours after the attack, rescuers were still working at the site, while residents tried to retrieve their belongings. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said the attacks showed the need for further international action against Russia, including enhanced global sanctions.",
