    "publishedAt": "2023-04-28T16:00:47Z",
    "content": "Sony has a great track record when it comes to budget headphones. The companys WH-CH710N\r\n were excellent, but overpriced initially. Sony made them an incredible value at $150 after it cut the price \u2026 [+7816 chars]",
    "summary": "Sony's WH-CH720N headphones are a solid contender in the mid-range headphone market, delivering great sound quality, comfortable design and a reasonable price point of $130. They feature physical controls, 35 hours of battery life, and Adaptive Sound Control that adjusts noise-cancelling and ambient sound settings based on location or activity. While the noise-cancelling feature is not as effective in blocking human voices as other headphones, the transparency mode offers a natural sound for video and voice calls. All in all, the WH-CH720N is a strong option for those looking for an affordable noise-cancelling headphone that doesn't skimp on features.",
