    "publishedAt": "2023-04-28T15:55:04Z",
    "content": "The Indianapolis Colts might finally be cured of their Andrew Luck hangover.\r\nWhen Luck retired, the Colts started on a path of acquiring second-chance veterans at the end of their careers, hoping to\u2026 [+9801 chars]",
    "summary": "The Indianapolis Colts have drafted quarterback Anthony Richardson with the fourth overall pick of the 2023 NFL Draft. Richardson, who has had only 13 college starts, is considered a high-risk, high-reward pick due to his all-world physical gifts and mechanical errors that negatively impacted his accuracy on the field. The Colts have Gardner Minshew II on the roster as a bridge QB, but there's little patience among fans, and it\u2019s hard to resist putting a physically gifted quarterback like Richardson in the lineup. The Colts are hoping quarterback Richardson will be their franchise-changing pick. In other news, teams have ignored criticisms aimed at positional value, with two teams drafting running backs in the first 12 picks. Jalen Carter, a Georgia defensive tackle, went to the Philadelphia Eagles with the No. 9 pick, while the Arizona Cardinals traded with the Houston Texans and got Paris Johnson Jr., an offensive lineman from Ohio State.",
