  "summary": "TL;DR: Early reactions to \"Guardians Of The Galaxy Vol. 3\" indicate that it is a genuine improvement over some of the recent Marvel releases and successfully recaptures some of the magic of early MCU films. The film smartly sticks to what works, prioritizing the found-family dynamic and crowd-pleasing needle drops, while also delivering moments of genuine pathos and some out-there character and set designs. Although it is a little too long and an uneven sensory overload, overall, the movie is entertaining, according to The A.V. Club. The film releases widely next week. ",
