  "summary": "The importance of human sports reporters was highlighted after a Bucks beat writer, Eric Nehm, asked Giannis Antetokounmpo a question that sparked a revealing two-minute response. Despite Mavericks owner Mark Cuban using the AI card to placate the anti-media crowd, there was a reminder of why fans should want objective reporters involved in the process. Giannis and Nehm\u2019s professional relationship gave the basketball star the context and comfort to share his perspective on the harsh reality of playing\u00a0professional sports. The need for talented scribes to ask complex questions to create fascinating discussions was emphasized as the message of the importance of unity in the NBA was driven home. ",
