  "publishedAt": "2023-04-28T11:54:05Z",
  "content": "Comment on this story\r\nComment\r\nLONDON The chairman of the BBC, Richard Sharp, announced his resignation on Friday following the release of an independent report that found he breached government rul\u2026 [+2759 chars]",
  "summary": "Richard Sharp, Chairman of the BBC, has resigned after an independent report found that he breached government rules by failing to declare his role in helping then-Prime Minister Boris Johnson obtain a personal loan. Sharp introduced Johnson to a wealthy supporter before his appointment as Chairman in 2021, leading to accusations of conflict of interest. Sharp denied any wrongdoing, calling his failure to declare his role inadvertent. A barrister's report found his involvement \"very limited\" and that there was no evidence he facilitated the loan. Critics say Sharp\u00a0sullied\u00a0the reputation of the BBC. ",
