  "title": "Bed Bath & Beyond store closures will kick off a land grab",
  "description": "Bed Bath & Beyond, which filed for bankruptcy, is expected to soon close hundreds of store locations.",
  "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2023/04/28/bed-bath-beyond-store-closures-land-grab.html",
  "urlToImage": "https://image.cnbcfm.com/api/v1/image/107231440-1682521977572-gettyimages-1484927640-bedbathbeyondfiledforbankruptcyprotection007.jpeg?v=1682679601&w=1920&h=1080",
  "publishedAt": "2023-04-28T11:00:01Z",
  "content": "In strip malls across the country, Bed Bath &amp; Beyond stores have \"Closing Soon\" signs.\r\nFor other retailers, those may as well be \"For Rent\" signs.\r\nThe home goods retailer, which filed for bankr\u2026 [+6110 chars]",
  "summary": "Home goods retailer Bed Bath & Beyond, which filed for bankruptcy, will create opportunities for retailers to gain new customers and market share as its nearly 500 locations open up for other companies to rent. Its stores are located in high-traffic suburban areas and could turn into a variety of other retail spaces, including Aldi and Lidl grocery locations or doctor offices for CVS and Walgreens. Weak retailers' locations thinned out during the pandemic, and now a mix of stronger retailers, including dollar stores, off-price retailers, direct-to-consumer players like Warby Parker, and traditional mall retailers like Macy's, are vying for space in similar strip centers. ",
